cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the management of intelligent things, including robots and agents, which falls under the domain of AI. 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper specifically mentions robots as one of the intelligent things that will be part of the networked workforce. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the challenges of managing mixed human-thing organizations, which requires understanding of human factors and interaction design. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the need for effective command and control (C2) functions in military organizations, which involves systems and control theory. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper briefly mentions the need for trust and security in managing mixed human-thing organizations, which could involve cryptography and security measures.
